7_Q2.8: The colander option didn't *not* make sense, but, given that the question was how to get water out of a coconut, technically I guess either answer could have been true - both described how to get the water out, although only one described how to catch it/keep it/contain it afterwards.  But even with a colander, you would have still gotten the water and performed the task in question. Also I think that perhaps not everyone has had experience getting water out of a coconut, so this might be based on culture (location, or, family culture/what groceries families buy and bring home).
